Topics Reviewed
DNS Security

DNS filtering

Prevents access to malicious or unsafe domains.

Protects users from phishing, malware distribution sites, and command-and-control servers.

Data Protection & Access Control

Access control policies ensure that only authorized personnel can access sensitive information.

Critical for protecting confidential and protected data.

Encryption Methods

Symmetric Encryption

Uses the same key for encryption and decryption.

Faster and more efficient than asymmetric encryption.

Often used for bulk data encryption.

Secure Communications

TLS (Transport Layer Security)

Encrypts data transmitted across networks.

Provides:

Confidentiality

Integrity

Authentication.

Log Analysis

Log Correlation

Combines and analyzes logs from multiple sources.

Helps identify patterns and security incidents that may not be visible in isolated logs.

Cloud Security Architecture

SASE (Secure Access Service Edge)

Integrates networking and security services.

Includes capabilities such as:

VPN

Secure web gateways

Firewall services

Zero trust network access.

Disaster Recovery

Simulated Failover Testing

Tests system resilience and disaster recovery capabilities.

Ensures services can continue operating during outages.

Malware Techniques

Memory Injection

Allows malicious code to execute in memory.

Often bypasses traditional file-based detection mechanisms.

Least Privilege

Implementing strict permission controls ensures users only access resources necessary for their role.

Security Auditing

Independent Security Audits

Provide an unbiased evaluation of security controls.

Often result in formal reports such as SOC reports to demonstrate control effectiveness.

